BED BATH & BEYOND INC. REPORTS RESULTS
FOR FISCAL FIRST QUARTER
 
                 
Net Earnings per Diluted Share of $.34 for Q1
                 
Quarterly Net Sales Increase by 2.8%
                 
Quarterly Comparable Store Sales Decrease by 1.6%
 
UNION, New Jersey, June 24, 2009  today reported net earnings of $.34 per diluted share ($87.2 million) in the fiscal first quarter ended May 30, 2009, compared with net earnings of $.30 per diluted share ($76.8 million) in the same quarter a year ago. Net sales for the fiscal first quarter of 2009 were approximately $1.694 billion, an increase of approximately 2.8% from net sales of $1.648 billion reported in the fiscal first quarter of 2008. Comparable store sales for the fiscal first quarter of 2009 decreased by approximately 1.6%.
Bed Bath & Beyond Inc.
 
As of May 30, 2009, the Company had a total of 1,044 stores, including 935 stores in 49 states, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico and Canada, 53 stores, 16 stores, and 40 stores under the names of or . During the fiscal first quarter, the Company opened six stores, one store, and one store and closed one store. Consolidated store space as of May 30, 2009 was approximately 32.2 million square feet. Since the beginning of the fiscal second quarter on May 31, 2009, three additional stores have been opened and one store has been closed. In addition, through a joint venture, the Company operates two stores in the Mexico City market under the name "."
